[?2004l[?2004h> - Primary group showing GID numbers instead of group names
[?2004l[?2004h> - Supplementary groups showing GID numbers instead of group names
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ROOT CAUSES (3 bugs identified):
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. BUG #1 - Wrong delimiter for emails.dat:
[?2004l[?2004h>    - emails.dat is TAB-delimited but script used space delimiter
[?2004l[?2004h>    - This caused the entire "UID<TAB>email" to be extracted as one field
[?2004l[?2004h>    - FIX: Changed from cut -d' ' to awk -F'\t' for proper tab handling
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. BUG #2 - Sorting mismatch (implicit in original design):
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Users sorted alphabetically by username, but emails needed lookup by UID
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Original script tried to paste by line number which mismatched
[?2004l[?2004h>    - FIX: Use awk to lookup email by UID match instead of line-based paste
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. BUG #3 - Wrong delimiter for groups.dat:
[?2004l[?2004h>    - groups.dat is COLON-delimited (gid:groupname:description)
